<Author>barolobrain
<Content>Service Is Superb My wife and I stayed for 6 nights during Golden Week. Due to difficulties in booking a room in Tokyo and Kyoto during this period, I had my co-worker in Shanghai go through her former PA in Tokyo to make the arrangements. We stayed in the original building The room had everything I look for, good light during the day, quiet at all times, comfortable beds, decent lighting, mini-bar and good internet connection.Service in the rooms, you know it's been done, you just don't know when or how. Concierge was very helpful in travel and cultural needs, English is not a problem. Business center rents out mobile phones for reasonable charges which can take your GSM SIM card and allow it to be used for calls within the Japan mobile system.Location is very good and is quiet and discreet. I found that it was an easy walk to Roppongi for night life and dining as well as to a number of Toei stops for access to the rest of Tokyo. Given how good the underground system is in Tokyo, we only used a cab when leaving the hotel for Kyoto.Hotel decor, bar and restaurants. The bar on ground floor is old school, dark and quiet, which I enjoy. Lot's of Japanese malt whiskey available. We ate at both the Tempura bar and the Sushi bar. Food, preparation and presentation were superb and decent value. Breakfast is served on the lower floor by the garden. It's primarily Western style with some Japanese available. It was quite crowded around 8:30AM when we were there but that may have been due to Golden Week.Not as flashy or new as some of the competition but a hotel I really enjoyed. It's on my preferred list for Tokyo above the Westin Ebisu which is a fine place and nice location, and the Dai-Ichi which is great value. Not on my list of places I have stayed, Park Hyatt which is expensive, in the middle of nowhere and unattractive Shinjuku (forget about Lost In The Translation, go for a drink and a snack-this location is for biz travelers only) and the Grand Hyatt which another grand Asian Hyatt, glossy and expensive. 
